{{Quote|So how do we play this? Like we did on Bakura? Or like that time on Lehon?|Venisa Doza, to Torch|audio=VenisaBakuraLehon-RendezvousPoint.flac|<ref name="SWR" />}}
'''Rakata Prime''', also known as '''Rakata''' and '''Lehon''', was the [[homeworld]] of the long-extinct [[Rakatan|Rakata]] [[species]], who were rumored to be the first to develop [[hyperspace]] travel, and was one of the few navigable [[Planet|worlds]] located in the [[Unknown Regions]]. The planet was [[orbit]]ed by a [[Rakata Prime refueling station|refueling station]]. At some point, the [[Resistance pilot]] [[Venisa Doza]] visited Lehon along with her [[astromech droid]], [[Torch]]. The [[Zabrak]] [[pirate]] [[Tryki]] was also once arrested for attempting to board a [[First Order]] [[cruiser]] near Rakata Prime.

==Description==
Lehon, also known as Rakata Prime,<ref name="SWKids">{{BucketsList|n7mLLqw_aFY|"Rendezvous Point"|date=2019-11-25}}</ref> or simply Rakata,<ref name="Hunters" /> was a terrestrial [[planet]]<ref name="SWKids" /> located in the [[Standard Galactic Grid|grid area]] G-11,<ref name="TFA BG" /> within the [[Unknown Regions]]'<ref name="TFA VD" /> [[Rakata Prime system]].<ref name="Appendix" /> Even though the cosmic bramble of [[Hyperspace anomaly|hyperspace anomalies]] known as the [[Galactic Barrier]] prevented the [[Scout|exploration]] of the region, Rakata Prime was one of the few navigable worlds that were found by rare exploratory missions, and the planet could be reached by cautiously stepped [[hyperspace]] jumps.<ref name="TROS VD">''[[Star Wars: The Rise of Skywalker: The Visual Dictionary]]''</ref>

==History==
{{Quote|Of course, if you believe the Legend of Lehon, Tatooine was once covered by lush jungle, the domain of the Kumumgah, although little evidence has been found for their existence.|A B'omarr monk|audio=LegendofLehon.flac|<ref name="AEM">''[[Choose Your Destiny: An Escape Mission]]''</ref>}}
[[File:VenisaTorch-RendezvousPoint.png|thumb|left|300px|Venisa Doza and Torch traveled to Lehon.]]
At some point no earlier than [[9 ABY]],<ref name="Hunters date">The events of ''[[Hunters: Battle for the Arena]]'' take place after [[Aran Tal]] joined the [[Hunters of the Outer Rim]], which ''[[Star Wars: Timelines]]'' dates to [[9 ABY]].</ref> the [[Force-sensitive]] [[Hunter (Grand Arena)|Hunter]] [[Rieve]] acquired an [[audiochip]] labeled ''[[The Blue Factory]]'', which contained [[gonkrock]] [[music]] performed by ''[[Corellia's Not Dead]]'', a [[band]] she once fronted. When she listened to her vocal performance in the recording, Rieve compared her screams and barks to some sort of beast from Rakata.<ref name="Hunters" />

By [[33 ABY]],<ref name="SWA date">''[[Star Wars Adventures, Volume 1: Heroes of the Galaxy]]'' establishes that [[Tryki]] was arrested near Rakata Prime before the [[kidnapping of Unkar Plutt]], which ''[[Star Wars: Timelines]]'' dates to [[33 ABY]].</ref> the [[Zabrak]] [[pirate]] [[Tryki]] was arrested for attempting to board a [[First Order]] [[cruiser]] near Rakata Prime, and her [[starship]] was destroyed as a result.<ref name="SWA">''[[Star Wars Adventures, Volume 1: Heroes of the Galaxy]]''</ref> The [[Resistance pilot]] [[Venisa Doza]] and her [[astromech droid]], [[Torch]], also once traveled to the planet. Later,<ref name="SWR" /> in [[34 ABY]],<ref name="SWT">''[[Star Wars: Timelines]]''</ref> when the duo was about to be captured by the First Order, Doza brought up their [[time]] on Lehon while planning how to [[Escape of Venisa Doza|escape]] their present predicament.<ref name="SWR" />

On one occasion no earlier than that [[Standard year|year]],<ref name="TUC date">{{UltimateCookbookDate}}</ref> the adventurous [[chef]] [[Strono Tuggs|Strono "Cookie" Tuggs]] traveled to a [[Rakata Prime refueling station|refueling station]] above Rakata Prime, where he enjoyed a cup of a strong [[caf]] known as [[Hyperspace Brew]], aboard his [[Tuggs' Grub Sienar-Chall Utilipede Transport|modified Sienar-Chall Utilipede Transport]]. Tuggs later mentioned the planet as well as his experience at the station above it in his recipe for the local drink published in ''[[The Ultimate Cookbook]]''<ref name="TUC" /> in [[35 ABY]].<ref name="TUC date" />

The world shared its names with the [[Timeline of galactic history|historical]] [[Infinite Empire|Rakatan Infinite Empire]],<ref name="NoP">''[[Nexus of Power]]''</ref> the mystical antiquities known as [[Rakatan wraith box]]es,<ref name="Solo Guide">''[[Solo: A Star Wars Story The Official Guide]]''</ref> and the [[Legend of Lehon]]. According to the legend,<ref name="AEM" /> the [[desert]] planet<ref name="SWT" /> [[Tatooine]] was once covered by lush [[jungle]] and inhabited by the [[Kumumgah]].<ref name="AEM" />

==Inhabitants==
{{Quote|The clerk kept goin' on about how the species that used to inhabit the world below invented hyperspace travel.|Strono Tuggs, ''The Ultimate Cookbook''|<ref name="TUC" />}}
Lehon was the [[Homeworld|home planet]] of an [[Amphibian|amphibious]] [[humanoid]] [[species]] known as the [[Rakatan|Rakata]],<ref name="BMF 47">{{BuildFalconCite|47|Secrets of Spaceflight}}</ref> or Rakatans,<ref name="TUC" /> who were the first in developing hyperspace travel, according to a legend. The species was said to be corrupted by the [[dark side of the Force]] a long time ago, and eventually went extinct.<ref name="BMF 47" /> The planet was also inhabited by beasts.<ref name="Hunters" />

==Locations==
{{Quote|Before settin' my course for Black Spire Outpost, I stopped at a refuelin' station above Rakata Prime.|Strono Tuggs, ''The Ultimate Cookbook''|<ref name="TUC" />}}
Rakata Prime was orbited by a [[Fuel|refueling]] [[Space station|station]] that employed a clerk.<ref name="TUC" />

==Behind the scenes==
{{Quote|Venisa mentions the planets Bakura and Lehon. Both have origins in fan-favorite ''Star Wars'' storytelling. Bakura is from the 1993 novel, ''The Truce at Bakura'', and Lehon is another name for Rakata Prime, a world from ''The Knights of the Old Republic'' video game.|The ''Bucket's List'' installment for "Rendezvous Point"|audio=BakuraLehon-BucketsList.flac|<ref name="SWKids" />}}
[[File:Unkwld_space.jpg|thumb|right|240px|Rakata Prime, as it appears in ''Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic'']]
Rakata Prime was first mentioned as Lehon&mdash;an alternate name for [[Lehon/Legends|Rakata Prime]] in the [[Star Wars Legends|''Star Wars'' Legends]] continuity<ref name="BLE">{{SW|url=news/buckets-list-extra-rendezvous-point-star-wars-resistance|text=Bucket's List Extra: 7 Fun Facts from "Rendezvous Point" - ''Star Wars Resistance''|date=2019-11-25|quote=Venisa makes mention of Bakura and Lehon; both worlds have origins in fan-favorite ''Star Wars'' Legends storytelling. Bakura was first featured in the 1993 novel, ''The Truce at Bakura'', and Lehon is another name for Rakata Prime, a world from the ''Knights of the Old Republic'' videogame.}}</ref>&mdash;in the current ''[[Star Wars]]'' [[canon]] in the [[Star Wars: Build the Millennium Falcon 47|forty-seventh issue]] of the ''[[Star Wars: Build the Millennium Falcon]]'' series of magazine, published by [[De Agostini]]<ref name="BMF 47" /> around [[November 25]], [[2015]].<ref name="BMF 47 date">{{BMFdates|47}}</ref> The name Rakata Prime was later introduced to canon on a [[map]] of [[the galaxy]]<ref name="Empire Magazine">{{WebCite|url=https://www.empireonline.com/movies/news/exclusive-empire-reveals-new-star-wars-planets|text=Exclusive: Empire reveals names of new Star Wars planets|author=De Semlyen, Phil|date=2015-11-26|work=[[Wikipedia:Empire (magazine)|''Empire'']]|archivedate=20160507021312}}</ref> created for ''[[Star Wars: The Force Awakens: The Visual Dictionary]]'',<ref name="Hidalgo tweet">{{Twitter|pablohidalgo|status/669926716974870528|[[Pablo Hidalgo]]|date=2015-11-26|quote=WARNING, INCOMING PLUG: That galaxy map was generated for the TFA Visual Dictionary, btw. PLUG COMPLETE.|archivefile=File:Pablo_Hidalgo_Canon_Map.png|nolive=1}}</ref> a reference book written by the [[Lucasfilm Story Group]]'s [[Pablo Hidalgo]] for the film {{Film|VII}} and released on [[December 18]], 2015.<ref name="DK">{{DK|url=us/book/9781465438164-star-wars-the-force-awakens-the-visual-dictionary|text=Star Wars: The Force Awakens The Visual Dictionary}}</ref> The aforementioned map was initially revealed prior to the book's release through an article by [[Wikipedia:Empire (magazine)|''Empire'']] magazine on [[November 26]], 2015.<ref name="Empire Magazine" /> The [[2023]] novel ''[[Hunters: Battle for the Arena]]'' also identified the planet simply as Rakata.<ref name="Hunters" />

Rakata Prime originally first appeared in the [[2003]] Legends [[Star Wars video games|video game]] ''[[Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic]]'' as the "Unknown World."<ref name="KotOR">''[[Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic]]''</ref> The [[2005]] reference book ''[[The New Essential Chronology]]'', written by [[Daniel Wallace]], introduced the name Rakata Prime,<ref name="TNEC">''[[The New Essential Chronology]]''</ref> while the [[2006]] novel ''[[Darth Bane: Path of Destruction]]'', written by [[Drew Karpyshyn]], introduced the name Lehon.<ref name="PoD">''[[Darth Bane: Path of Destruction]]''</ref> Later in 2006, the reference book ''[[The New Essential Guide to Alien Species]]'' first identified the planet simply as Rakata.<ref name="TNEGtAS">''[[The New Essential Guide to Alien Species]]''</ref>

